        <ul id="ul_eds_ppt_vjb" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/C:/Users/bronagh.moynihan/Desktop/Certificate%20IDD/DITA%20project/open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements.dita" xtrc="ul:5;31:33">
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/C:/Users/bronagh.moynihan/Desktop/Certificate%20IDD/DITA%20project/open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements.dita" xtrc="li:12;32:17">vCPU: 4 Even though increasing the number of vCPUs increases performance, the actual
                benefits depend on whether the specific host is oversubscribed or not. </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/C:/Users/bronagh.moynihan/Desktop/Certificate%20IDD/DITA%20project/open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements.dita" xtrc="li:13;34:17">Memory: 16 GB While the minimum value works under light-load condition, as the load
                increases, the data server quickly starts using swap space. For high load
                situations, increasing RAM beyond 16 GB can benefit performance. Monitoring swap
                usage can provide insight. </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/C:/Users/bronagh.moynihan/Desktop/Certificate%20IDD/DITA%20project/open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements.dita" xtrc="li:14;38:17">Storage:<ul id="ul_lwf_spt_vjb" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/C:/Users/bronagh.moynihan/Desktop/Certificate%20IDD/DITA%20project/open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements.dita" xtrc="ul:6;38:49">
